If interviewer asks:

“What happens when you type a URL and hit enter?”

Correct structure:

DNS resolution

TCP/TLS connection

HTTP request

Load balancer

Web server

App server

Framework (Django)

DB

Response back

If you start with:

“It goes to urls.py…”

============================

Now technical.

Nginx

A web server + reverse proxy

Handles:

Incoming connections

Static files (CSS, JS, images)

Load balancing

SSL termination

It is written in C, very fast, non-blocking.

Gunicorn

WSGI server (Web Server Gateway Interface)

Used for sync Django / Flask

It runs multiple Python worker processes

Each worker handles one request at a time

Best for:

Traditional Django apps

Uvicorn

ASGI server (Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface)

Used for:

FastAPI

Async Django

WebSockets

Best for:

Real-time apps, async, high concurrency